snippet.textDisplay:
He dissed Glee but praised Devil Wears Prada. I don't know if I can watch this channel anymore.
Seriously though, I really appreciate how Alex Meyers is a guy but has no shame in his interest of girly shows. Like he makes fun of them sure but he obviously wouldn't watch them if he wasn't going to expect to like them. I just don't like it when all girly movies and shows and books are regarded as bad because they're girly. For example my Dad is in his fifties, never read Pride and Prejudice because even though it was a classic and nearly one of the most famous period novels of all time, didn't think he'd like it because it was girly. We watched it when the movie came on the TV (that's the same time I fell in love with it), my Dad went bananas for it. Not because it was romantic, or a masterful film or an excellent historical piece or full of action like so many macho movies that guys drool over. No he was surprised at how intelligent the story was an all the wit that went on in it and how using that wit, Austen had made really boring plot lines the most intelligent thing he'd ever seen.
Moral of the story, don't discredit something's intelligence just because girls are into it. But you guys all know that are you wouldn't be watching this channel.

Idiot: "Here's an unlimited 7-Day Subscription!"

Me: "What do you mean by unlimited?"

Idiot: "It is unlimited... For 7 days"

Me: "You're limiting it to 7 days, therefore it is limited."

Idiot: "Shut up and give me your money!"

Me: "No thanks. I'll go somewhere else."
